In lfs_fs_parent the local variable 'err' is initialized at declaration with int err = LFS_ERR_OK;. That initial assignment is never used: the first assignment to err occurs inside the while loop (err = lfs_tortoise_detectcycles(...)) before any read of err, and on the path where the loop is not entered the initialized value is also never used. Therefore the initialization is an executed operation whose removal would not affect program behaviour (it is redundant/dead), violating MISRA C 2023 Rule 2.2.
</scenario>

